# API and Data Handling Guidelines

## Data Fetching

- Use Next.js App Router for API routes
- Implement proper error handling for API calls
- Use proper loading states during data fetching
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use proper data validation with Zod

## API Structure

- Place API routes in the `app/api` directory
- Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Implement proper error responses
- Use proper status codes
- Implement proper rate limiting

## Data Validation

- Use Zod for schema validation
- Implement proper type checking
- Use proper error messages
- Implement proper form validation
- Use proper data sanitization

## State Management

- Use React Query for server state
- Use proper caching strategies
- Implement proper optimistic updates
- Use proper error handling
- Implement proper loading states

## Security

- Implement proper authentication
- Use proper authorization
- Implement proper CORS policies
- Use proper input validation
- Implement proper rate limiting
- Use proper error handling
- Implement proper logging

## Performance

- Implement proper caching
- Use proper data pagination
- Implement proper data prefetching
- Use proper data compression
- Implement proper error boundaries

## Testing

- Write proper unit tests
- Implement proper integration tests
- Use proper mocking strategies
- Implement proper error testing
- Use proper performance testing


- Do Not Write Comments
- Do Not use HardCoded Colors
- If you are not sure, stop and ask
- Use PNPM please
